    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.17.4" />
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">4</fw>
                
                
                <opener>
                <dateline>Branson, Mo.
                May 4
                1 9 3 3 </dateline>
                
                <address>
                <addrLine>Mr. Clark McAdams</addrLine>
                <addrLine>Post-Dispatch</addrLine>
                <addrLine>St. Louis, Mo.</addrLine>
                </address>
                
                <salute>Dear Mr. McAdams:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>It was impossible to get another leader to you <add>Friday</add> <del>yesterday</del> morning. This did not occur to me while we were talking on the 'phone Thursday afternoon. I hope it will be possible to use the enclosed this week. I know Gottlieb will see that the proof is correct.</p>
                
                <p>I'm really sorry that the Masters article seems objectionable, but I'm sure you have good reasons. Never was a time more thoroughly bedevelled with <add><del/>false</add> <del>false</del> prophets in all fields, and it seems worthwhile to help a little<add>,</add> when<add>ever</add> possible, to discredit them.</p>
                
                <p>I was serious about your dropping in here and being around with us. You'd like it, I hope, and we would, I know.</p>
                  <closer>  
                    <salute>Yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>John G. Neihardt</signed>
                    
                    
                    
                    
                    
                    <note>JGN:EN<lb/>
                    Enc. 1</note>
                  </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
        
